                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus from="2ra" to="5vb"/>
                           <desc type="CommemorativeNote">Register of those who make the commemoration of the Martyrs of
                              Ṗarāqliṭos.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> ጸሐፍና፡ አስማቲሆሙ፡ ለእለ፡ ይገብሩ፡ ተዝከሮሙ፡ ለሰማዕተ፡
                              ጳራቅሊጦስ፡...</q>
                           
                           <note> In this note, the name Ṗarāqliṭos is written as Ṗaraqliṭos. It is possibly continued as <ref target="#a3"></ref>
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus from="5vb" to="6vb"/>
                           <desc type="GuestText"><title ref="LIT5880SalamParaqlitos">salām-hymn for the Martyrs of Ṗarāqliṭos</title></desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ሰላም፡ ለክሙ፡ ሰማዕታተ፡ ጰራቅሊጦስ፡ ናር፡ እለ፡
                              ጥብርያዶስ፡ ብሔር፡…</q>
                           
                           <note> The note is crudely written in a <ref target="#h3" type="hand">16th-cent. (?) hand</ref>. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#44vb">f. 44vb (above)</locus>
                           <desc type="CommemorativeNote">Note on the commemoration
                              of the Martyrs of Ṗarāqliṭos (?).</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ወቀዳሚ፡ ዘገብረ፡ ተዝካሮሙ፡ አቡየ፡
                              ሄኖክ።</q>
                           
                           <note> The note, written in a hand very similar to <ref type="hand" target="#h2">the main one</ref> (the
                              same?), states that "my father" Henok is the first one to have done
                              “their commemoration”. Possibly it is the end of <ref target="#a1">Additio 1</ref>. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#44vb">f. 44vb (below)</locus>
                           <desc type="ScribalSupplication">Supplication for the scribe (?).</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ወዛቲ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ዘፃሕየየ። ይፃሕይይ። ወይጽሐፍ። ስሞ፡ ውስተ፡
                              መጽሐፈ፡ ሕይወት። ወኢትርሥዕዎ፡ ፩፩አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት።</q>
                           
                           <note> The note has been written over an erasure. For ፃሕየየ (ḍāḥyaya),s. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Leslau1987dic"/><citedRange>553b</citedRange></bibl>
                             </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#86vb"></locus>
                           <desc type="MixedNote">Short note (biblical quotation?). </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              &lt;...&gt; ሠናየ፡ ግበሩ፡ ቢጸክሙ፡ አፍቅሩ፡
                              እስመ፡ ዘአ[ፍ]ቀረ፡ ቢጾ፡ ይነሥእ፡ </q>

                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>- Title (ጻድቃን?) is crudely written in green on the front
